result.execSummary:
The defendant Kimberly Ruth Okey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kimberly Ruth Okey is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kimberly Ruth Okey was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kimberly Ruth Okey in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that an offer has been provided and the defendant would like to accept that offer.  Defendant agrees.  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 2.  Ct. 1 to be dismissed.
  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives their right to an attorney.    Court finds waiver made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty to Ct. 2.  Ct. 1 to be dismissed.

Atty Hendee asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 2:  Pay fine and costs = $379.00
DNA Sample + $200 Surcharge
bond to be applied
  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan for balance:  $50.00/month commencing in February

Ct. 1 to be dismissed.

Pre-trial conference at 11-10-2015 10:00 am.
Return date at 12-16-2015 03:30 pm.

Defendant Kimberly Ruth Okey in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant understands her rights.  Court finds probable cause.

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.
